<p><a name="top"></a></p>
<h1>ESSUM37200 - Approval of schemes: Applications for approval</h1>
<p>There is no prescribed application form, however there is <strong>an informal review document</strong>&nbsp;<u></u>(<a href="attachments/essum38802_checklist.doc">checklist (Word 125kb)</a>) that should be used to demonstrate that the legislation governing approved SAYE share option schemes is satisfied (see ESSUM38902). Applications should be supported by whatever evidence an officer of HM Revenue &amp; Customs requires (paragraph 1). The documentary evidence generally required is set out in the Shareschemes section of the HMRC web-site and summarised on the front page of the <a href="attachments/essum38802_checklist.doc">checklist (Word 125kb)</a>.</p>
<p>Applications for approval can be made by any body corporate (UK resident or otherwise) which has established a share option scheme. Guidance on establishing schemes is at <a href="ESSUM37400.htm">ESSUM37400</a>.</p>
<p>Foreign companies may wish to establish schemes for employees of their UK subsidiary companies. Whilst it will be rare for a foreign scheme to satisfy the requirements of Schedule 3, it may be possible for</p>
<ul>
<li>the subsidiary company or companies to set up free-standing schemes which fully satisfy Schedule 3,  or</li>
<li>an addendum to be made to the parent companyâ€™s foreign scheme, to disapply the unacceptable features of the foreign scheme and to import the rules which are required to satisfy Schedule 3 (see ESSUM37400).</li>
</ul>
<p>Before submitting a scheme for formal approval the company should provide draft documentation in order that ESSU can review all scheme documentation to ensure that it is in a form capable of approval (see <a href="ESSUM11100.htm">ESSUM11100</a>). Once this review is completed ESSU will advise of any changes needed and in due course advise when the scheme is in a form capable of approval. It is at this point that the scheme should be formally adopted by the company and application made for formal approval. It is possible for schemes to be approved before appointing a savings carrier; however the approval letter will be suitably endorsed to the effect that documentation in relation to the linked savings arrangement has still to be formally reviewed. Invitations should not be issued until such time as this documentation has also been formally approved (see <a href="ESSUM11250.htm">ESSUM11250</a>). </p><br><div class="manual-nav">
